    <name>
      <text>Determining common logarithms using a calculator</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p> During a mathematics lesson, a Grade 10 learner uses a calculator to find the common logarithm of the number
\({@num@}\). Find <strong>\(\log_{10}({@num@})\)</strong>.</p>

<p><em>Enter your answer as a single whole number.</em></p>
<p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
The common logarithm is a logarithm to base 10.
</p>

<p>
\[
\log_{10}({@num@}) = {@correct_ans@}
\]
</p>

<p>
This means that:
</p>

<p>
\[
10^{{@correct_ans@}} = {@num@}
\]
</p>

<p>
The value can be obtained using a calculator or logarithm tables.
</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
